31/05/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- The 15th annual general assembly of the European Foundation Centre opened on Monday (31 May) with Deputy UN Secretary General Louise Frechette noting an urgent need to upgrade the role of the UN. 
She wants to make it more effective in addressing threats to world security in the 21st century. 
Athens 2004 Olympic Games Organising Committee President Gianna Angelopoulos-Daskalaki welcomed the delegates, saying such events would help transform Athens into a modern, cosmopolitan capital.
In other news, a replica of a 3,500-year-old wooden boat set sail from Crete to be showcased during the Olympics. 
It was built using clues left on ancient inscriptions and artwork. 
(ANA, MPA - 31/05/04; AP - 30/05/04)
